SIMPLE: infinitude
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Infinitude
<hw>In*fin"i*tude</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
quality or state of being infinite, or without limits;
infiniteness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Infinite extent; unlimited space; immensity;
infinity.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧I am who fill <xex>infinitude</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As pleasing to the fancy, as speculations of eternity or
<qex>infinitude</qex> are to the understanding.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Boundless number; countless multitude.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧An <xex>infinitude</xex> of distinctions.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infinituple</ent>⟦br⟧
